trend_summary: Over the sequence, the small waterside settlement grows slowly. A handful of new houses and sheds appear along the main road while most farmland persists. Piers multiply and lengthen, indicating increased recreational boating. Tree cover thickens around wetlands and some marginal fields. The area stays sparsely built and distinctly rural.
notable_changes: 5–10 additional rooftops added, mainly mid-peninsula along the north–south road.
Pier count and length increase markedly on the eastern shoreline.
Tree canopy expands south and west of the village, suggesting natural regeneration.
One small agricultural plot near the bridge shows abandonment and revegetation.
Road surface near the bridge appears upgraded, with brighter, wider pavement.
